r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKW-SPARKS-LADN-(SLAN     06-11 0317
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKW-SPARKS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPARKS RUN TO A RECORD IN OPENER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAMELA LEWIS  
 c.1999 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ For openers, the Los Angeles Sparks made a
pretty good first impression as they dismantled the Sacramento
Monarchs to kick off their third WNBA season Thursday night at the
Forum.
</P>
<P>
   It was a new look for the Sparks, who used outstanding defense
and a balanced offense to rout the Monarchs 100-78 before a crowd
of 8,262. Six players scored in double figures, with Lisa Leslie
leading with 19. Ukari Figgs and Tamecka Dixon had 14 each and
DeLisha Milton, Allison Feaster and reserve Mwadi Mabika had 11
apiece.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very happy,'' Sparks coach Orlando Woolridge said. ``I
thought at the beginning of the game we got caught up in the
emotion of the game. Once we calmed down and picked up the defense,
we were a lot more poised.''
</P>
<P>
   In compiling a franchise high for points in a game, the Sparks
got everyone involved, with Figgs running the point and Penny Toler
backing her up. Even Yugoslavian Gordana Grubin, who arrived
Wednesday night from Hungary, got into the action late in the game.
She pulled up for a 10-foot jumper with 6.8 seconds left for the
Sparks' final basket.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks picked apart the Monarchs, opening the game with a
10-0 run and leading by 21 with 10:18 to go. They led by 24 twice.
</P>
<P>
   ``They sort of wore us down,'' said Monarchs coach Sonny Allen.
``You have to give their defense credit. They have good depth
inside.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks shot 53 percent from the field, including 10 of 18
from 3-point range.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks' previous single-game high was 93 points against the
Monarchs two years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Yugoslavian Nina Bjedov, who was obviously fatigued after
arriving in Los Angeles just hours before the game, was the only
Sparks player who didn't see action.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
