<SLUG> BC-STATES-AWARDS-PA </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, June 10 --
The Boeing Co. of Philadelphia won a $99,900 contract from the Navy
in Philadelphia for yoke assemblies.
</P>
<P>
   Derbyshire Machine and Tool Co. of Philadelphia won a $37,605
contract from the Navy in Mechanicsburg for lock seal assemblies.
</P>
<P>
   SKF Industries of Kulpsville won a $58,000 contract from the
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for bearings.
</P>
<P>
   Del San Environmental Services Inc. of Bath won a $372,000
contract from the Dept. of Health and Human Services in Seattle,
Wash., for property maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $119,791 contract from
the Defense General SUpply Center in Richmond, Va. for aircraft
components.
</P>
<P>
   News Printing Co. Inc. of Claysburg won a $433,515 contract from
the Government Printing Office in Chicago, Ill., for printing.
</P>
<P>
   Kampi Components Co., of Bristol won a $99,650 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for constuction equipment.
</P>
<P>
   AEB Services Inc. of Oakmont won a $68,002 contract from the
Defens Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for mechanical equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Mova Pharmaceutical Corporation of Penndel won a $100,000
contract from the Dept. of Veterans Affairs in Hines, Ill., for
pharmaceuticals.
</P>
