the base where the B-2 bombers flew from during the air war in
Yugoslavia. By James Dao.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ALBRIGHT (Skopje, Macedonia) _ Madeleine K. Albright, who
had made the return of the ethnic Albanian refugees the major
mission of the Kosovo war, met face to face with them for the first
time Friday. She hugged some of them, shook hands, and as she
passed along a rope line holding back exuberant crowds, shouted:
``You'll be going home.'' By Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ALBANIA (Kukes, Albania) _ The scene from the Albanian
border where planning continues for what is expected to be the
chaotic re-entry of refugees to their homes and villages. By Ian
Fisher.
