   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GUN-CONTROL (Washington) _ Many amendments are offered to gun
control legislation by the noon deadline, illustrating the
divisiveness and confusion over the House effort to pass
legislation. By Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   EDUC-TESTING (Washington) _ The Department of Education's draft
of recommendations on how schools can avoid discrimination suits if
standardized tests such as the SAT's, produce racially disparate
results has drawn the ire of conservatives. Critics claim that in
proferring the advice, the Department is telling schools not to use
such tests at all. By Steven A. Holmes.
</P>
