information _ particularly credit card account numbers _ with
telemarketers amid a growing crackdown by federal and state
regulators on potentially abusive practices. By Timothy J. O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ECON (Tokyo) _ The Japanese Government unveiled a laundry
list of proposals to make the job market more dynamic, speed
corporate restructuring and create more than 700,000 jobs but did
not say how much it would spend on the program, leaving the plan's
potential power to spur the economy somewhat mysterious. By
Stephanie Strom.
