<P>
   COWTOWN HERD &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ When the Fort Worth cattle herd leaves
downtown for its ceremonial trek to the Stockyards on Saturday,
Cathy Cannon will be alongside the longhorns _ every nervous step
of the way. She changed careers to be part of this cattle drive.
She took a salary cut to work the steers daily, and now she labors
nights and weekends to supplement her income and recover her
losses. Cannon is one of six full-time drovers who will push the
newly formed Fort Worth Herd down North Main Street toward Exchange
Avenue in celebration of the city's 150th birthday. On Monday, the
15-head herd will become a permanent tourist attraction in the
Stockyards. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CARMAX &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LANCASTER, Texas _ It's been an uphill battle, but CarMax Auto
Superstores has finally turned a small profit. One auto analyst
said that the chain's concept of no-haggle pricing and
customer-friendly sales practices has had a big impact on the
industry, it's just a question of whether CarMax can stick around
long enough to reap the benefits. By BOB COX. Story has moved in
``f'' financial category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
