   RELIGION-JONES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The hottest TV evangelist at the moment is Benny Hinn,
a spirit-filled crusader known for the practice of touching people
on the forehead with his palm, causing them to fall backward as if
``slain in the spirit.'' And his announcement that he will move his
headquarters to Fort Worth-Dallas from Orlando, Fla., was good news
for both his advocates and his naysayers. Critics such as Ole
Anthony, president of a watchdog organization in Dallas, won't have
to go as far to investigate Hinn's international evangelism
operation. By JIM JONES. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
