relationship with the press. He snarled at reporters about their
coverage of his father's 1992 presidential campaign. Now, after
years of reaping ``good press'' as Texas governor, he says the
Texas media respect him. But as Bush starts campaigning for
president, he may go back to square one. Longtime observers of
presidential campaign coverage say the national press is ready to
pounce on the governor. By ALAN BERNSTEIN. (Already filed.)
