   &QL; 
JACUZZI_ Jacuzzi Ltd. was founded in the 1910s as a propeller
company and moved into whirlpool baths after a pump was
jerry-rigged in a bathtub for an injured family member. The
company, based in Walnut Creek, became a cultural icon in the
groovy, spa-happy 1970s and then fell off the radar screen. Now
owned by U.S. Industries, a New Jersey-based conglomerate, Jacuzzi
continues to sell its whirlpool baths as well as new high-end
products such as steaming shower stalls and some surprises, like
agricultural irrigation systems. By Carol Emert
</P>
